comment:
(Heads up: I have posted this on several videos, hoping that Lost Beyond Pluto might see it. Sorry for the spamming) 

Dear Lost Beyond Pluto, I miss watching your legal analysis and professional translations of all the "legaleze" into layman terms for us. 
I get that you are clearly having much more fun with your current format of talk show with someone you care about and feel comfortable with. It clearly shows, and you look like you are having such a good time. And I want that for you. 

I just miss having your unique and sharp and simple breakdowns of a case that has been so complicated and felt so confusing (the AH/JD case). 
As someone who is still living with long-term consequences of prolonged emotional abuse (it's nearly 20 years later and I am still having a hard time trusting anyone or even functioning as an adult), this case really got to me. Hearing those tapes really punched me in the gut, emotionally. 
One of the things that have been so devastating for me, is that no-one believed me, and that's what I see repeated with Depp. 
...and the let-down and despondency so many victims of abuse felt collectively after the UK ruling...! Well I know I'm not the only one who took that really hard. 

I continue to follow this case because I am so personally invested, but I really miss your expert, clear-cut and qualified analysis and take on the developments. 
I would so much like to hear your opinion on the paper that just came out, using the UK ruling as a case study and minutely and systematically assessing the credibility of AH. The paper is called "Assessment of Credibility of Testimony in Alleged Intimate Partner Violence: A Case Study" and can be found here https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/24732850.2021.1945836

comment:
I feel that Jennifer's statement could carry a lot of weight for a couple of reasons. One: she was supeonaed (sp?) So, no axe to grind. 
Two: Forget the stairs incident or any of that. The fact that Whitney (and amber?) said that whitney had to go sleep on her employer's floor and Jennifer says that SHE is that employer. But whitney slept in a guest room, discredits whitney's (and amber's ~ AGAIN) testemony completely. 
That is all I need from Jennifer's statement. 
But, I guess there is a little bit of icing. I would tend to believe Jennifer's statements where she says whitney said she wanted to stay with her because she was afraid if amber.  And that she was surprised Johnny puts up with amber and the explanation of the stairs incident are true. It seems that they were good friends. I think that while venting, especially venting fear, people don't lie to friends as close as whitney and Jennifer were. whitney said this to Jennifer BEFORE there was any thought of a court case (I think). So, she would have no reason to lie. Plus, she, whitney would have been lying in favor of Johnny which would get her in more trouble with her sister, amber. Who, I truly believe whitney was afraid of. Also, whitney said she was afraid amber would push Johnny down the stairs. This aligns with a statement I think whitney made in court that.....I'm so confused as to sequence....but, at some point whitney placed herself between Johnny and amber. But, she was facing AWAY from Johnny and AT amber. People face the person they are afraid of. For whitney to put her back to Johnny and face amber shows me that she was not afraid of Johnny pushing her. But of amber pushing or hitting her or Johnny. So, she faced the person she was afraid of.....amber.
The above explanation by whitney aligns with the statement to Jennifer that she, whitney was afraid of amber. She was afraid for herself and for Johnny. 

But, the strongest support from this statement is that neither whitney or amber are credible because its MORE credible evidence that whitney and amber lied on the stand. (Sleeping on the floor vs sleeping in a guest room.)

I actually feel sorry for whitney. If amber is THAT violent. Which it sound like she is, I could easily see whitney being terrified if she didn't say what amber told her to say. Under other circumstances, I might tend to think that whitney is not all that bad and that she would not have lied had she not been terrified of amber. 

The whole thing sucks!

comment:
Sorry, I am late to the dance. I did not know why I was being copied your opinion of this matter.

Quickly, with my existing knowledge of the subject matter and this current post.

It Is your contention that this 3rd party HEARSAY evidence will be accepted into court and considered in this civil suit against the so-called, NEWS?paper recognized as, The Sun.

You are further stating that said 3rd party, HEARSAY evidence will be accepted in a similar civil suit against Amber Heard in the United States.

As the president of Fathers4Justice, I am familiar with both courts, however, I primarily deal in matters of family law. 

Much of what is being stated is of course HEARD in matters of family law and even though as many as 80% of the family law judges queried on the subject matter believe that allegations of abuse in family law are false, they still accept said allegations as a result of the BILLIONS of dollars generated in family law and specifically in this matter, the BILLIONS of dollars generated for the states via both VAWA and the Social Security Act's title iv-d program.

The bottom line is always the same, will the courts. the attorney's and all of their minions generate income as a result of said, "hearsay evidence'?

Legally admissible and believable or not, there is money to br made here.With that said, it is my contention that said evidence will be admitted. NOT BASED ON MATTERS. OF LAW but on matters of income generated by every facet of the case, including the drama.

The statements made here within your video do not discuss the validity of any comments made by the Sun and I am not familiar with, nor have I followed your previous videos. However, Anyone familiar with said, NEWS?paper is fully well aware of the anti-male gender-biased and drama based posts of said, NEWS?paper. 

In our campaign for family law reform we subscribe and communicate with both broadcast and print media worldwide. When communicating any matters with UK media, we must be 'matter of fact'. Therefore, we make it a point not to communicate with the SUN.

We are all looking forward to the complete vindication of Mr. Depp of these false allegations and more importantly, full accountability for the criminal falsehoods as perpetrated by Ms. Amber Heard.

I wish you continued success in your efforts and will try and follow along as time allows.

JUSTICE IS COMING!!!
